Key Match Events: Jayson Tatum hit a 3-pointer at the buzzer in overtime as the Boston Celtics rallied to beat the Toronto Raptors 126-123.
Jaylen Brown added 27 points. Al Horford and Derrick White scored 18 points apiece.
Jakob Poeltl scored a career-high 35 points and finished 16 of 19 from the field with 12 rebounds.
With the game tied at 112 in regulation, RJ Barrett connected on a runner in the lane and was fouled by Brown with 59 seconds remaining, but missed his ensuing free throw.
Neemias Queta, who started in place of Jrue Holiday, scored a driving layup on Boston’s next possession.

With the game tied at 123, Toronto won a coach’s challenge on an out of bounds call that originally was awarded to Boston, but Barrett had his driving layup attempt blocked by Queta, giving the ball back to the Celtics with 20.2 seconds remaining.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Raptors outscored the Celtics 76-42 in the paint.
Toronto has lost seven straight and failed to register its first road win of the season.
The Celtics improved to 11-3 and avoided losing for the third time at TD Garden this season.
